SEC. 15.

Rules and Regulations.

â Consistent with the policy of promoting transparency in PERA investment and thereby affording protection to the Contributor, the Department of Finance, the Bureau of Internal Revenue and the concerned Regulatory Authorities, with the Bangko Sentral ng Pilipinas as lead agency, shall coordinate to establish uniform rules and regulations pertaining to the following subject matters:

Qualification and disqualification standards for Administrators, Custodians and Investment Managers, including directors and officers thereof;

Qualified and/or eligible PERA investment products;

Valuation standards for PERA investments;

Disclosure requirements on the terms and conditions of the PERA investments;

Minimum requirements imposed on the Administrators as regards inculcating financial literacy in investors;

Ascertainment of client suitability for PERA products;

Fees to be charged by the Administrator, Custodian or Investment Manager shall always be reasonable and approved by the concerned Regulatory Authority;

SEC. 17.

Penalty.

â A fine of not less than Fifty thousand pesos (P50,000.00) nor more than Two hundred thousand pesos (P200,000.00) or imprisonment of not less than six (6) years and one (1) day to not more than twelve (12) years or both such fine and imprisonment, at the discretion of the court, shall be imposed upon any person, association, partnership or corporation, its officer, employee or agent, who, acting alone or in connivance with others, shall:

Act as Administrator, Custodian or Investment Manager without being properly qualified or without being granted prior accreditation by the concerned Regulatory Authority;

Invest the contribution without written or electronically authenticated authority from the Contributor, or invest the contribution in contravention of the instructions of the Contributor;

Knowingly and willfully make any statement in any application, report, or document required to be filed under this Act, which statement is false or misleading with respect to any material fact:

Misappropriate or convert, to the prejudice of the Contributor, contributions to and investments or income from the PERA;
